onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: Whenever an {IERC721} `tokenId` token is transferred to this contract via {IERC721-safeTransferFrom} by `operator` from `from`, this function is called. It must return its Solidity selector to confirm the token transfer. If any other value is returned or the interface is not implemented by the recipient, the transfer will be reverted. The selector can be obtained in Solidity with `IERC721Receiver.onERC721Received.selector`.

MAX_K().notice: Constants used to calculate Blunt Finance fee

bluntProjectId().notice: The ID of the Blunt Finance project.

closeRound().notice: Close blunt round if target has been reached: - Pay BF fee,  - Reconfigure next FC, - Transfer project NFT to projectOwner. If called when totalContributions hasn't reached the target, disables payments and keeps full redemptions enabled.

didPay((address,uint256,uint256,(address.notice: Part of IJBPayDelegate, this function gets called when the project receives a payment.  It checks if blunt round hasn't been closed and hasn't reached the deadline.

didRedeem((address,uint256,uint256,uint2.notice: Part of IJBRedemptionDelegate, this function gets called when the beneficiary redeems tokens.  It will update storage if conditions are met.

isTargetReached().notice: Returns true if total contributions received surpass the round target.

payParams((address,address,(address,uint.notice: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource, this function gets called when the project receives a payment. It will set itself as the delegate to get a callback from the terminal.

redeemParams((address,address,uint256,ui.notice: Part of IJBFundingCycleDataSource, this function gets called when a project's token holders redeem. It will return the standard properties.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Indicates if this contract adheres to the specified interface.
